                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d74">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/3540a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Weddell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-02-14T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 14, 1934—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>22. Please ascertain if possible and cable Department the opinion of the League
                    Commission regarding Paraguayan proposal to Bolivia and Bolivian
                    counterproposal, and in particular whether in its opinion any advance has been
                    made as the result of the formulation of these proposals. The Department would
                    also be glad to have any opinions which may have been expressed to you with
                    regard thereto by the Argentine Minister for Foreign Affairs.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
